<subSubSection id="52BB49D6FF97FF85B68BFA62A77FFE92" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF97FF86B68BFA62A02DF9A9" blockId="1.[174,1233,1462,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">
Diagnosis. This species is characterized by the irregularly granulate metasoma (as on 
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF97FF86B6C6FA02A493FA29" box="[174,230,1494,1521]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[170,203,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[305,1093,562,1688]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[305,1093,558,1689]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig.1.Delomerista spp.1–2 —habitus,lateralview:1—D.cf.japonica, female;2 — D.novita,male;3 —D. novita, female, dorsal view of propodeum; 4, 5 — dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite: 4 — D. pfankuchi, male; 5 — D. novita, female; 6–10 — lateral view of ovipositor tip: 6 — D. pfankuchi; 7 — D. borealis; 8 — D. mandibularis; 9 — D.cf. japonica; 10 — D.japonica (non-Carpathian material); 11–12 — lateral view of two basal antennal segments: 11 — D. borealis; 12 — D. mandibularis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B69BFA02A574FA28" box="[243,257,1494,1520]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">5</emphasis>
); the malar space which is about 0.5 × length of basal width of mandible; the yellow upper hind corner of pronotum and tegulae; the short and sloping down propodeum with area superomedia wider than long; the ovipositor which is about 1.4–1.6 × length of hind tibia, with rounded at apex upper valve (
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF97FF86B4F4F9E2A6AFF989" box="[668,730,1590,1617]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[170,203,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[305,1093,562,1688]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[305,1093,558,1689]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig.1.Delomerista spp.1–2 —habitus,lateralview:1—D.cf.japonica, female;2 — D.novita,male;3 —D. novita, female, dorsal view of propodeum; 4, 5 — dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite: 4 — D. pfankuchi, male; 5 — D. novita, female; 6–10 — lateral view of ovipositor tip: 6 — D. pfankuchi; 7 — D. borealis; 8 — D. mandibularis; 9 — D.cf. japonica; 10 — D.japonica (non-Carpathian material); 11–12 — lateral view of two basal antennal segments: 11 — D. borealis; 12 — D. mandibularis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454726/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B483F9E2A68CF988" box="[747,761,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">9</emphasis>
). Male is distinguisheble by the yellow malar space and tegulae and the small and broadly triangular area superomedia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF97FF86B68BF9A2A60EF949" blockId="1.[174,1233,1462,1841]" box="[227,635,1654,1681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Flight period in Carpathians. June.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF97FF85B68BF942A0BDFED2" blockId="1.[174,1233,1462,1841]" lastBlockId="2.[166,1225,175,330]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">
Remarks. This species is close to non-Carpathian examined 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF97FF86B5ADF943A038F968" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1937" box="[965,1101,1687,1712]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B5ADF943A038F968" box="[965,1101,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">D. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens and to 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF97FF86B76AF963A6CEF909" authority="(Gravenhorst, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[258,699,1718,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B76AF963A5B4F908" box="[258,449,1718,1744]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">D. mandibularis</emphasis>
(Gravenhorst, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the smaller body compared to most other 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF97FF86B75FF902A655F929" box="[311,544,1750,1777]" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B75FF902A5B6F928" box="[311,451,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">Delomerista</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, the antenna with only 20–21 segments (
<quantity id="DD59B7B8FF97FF86B26CF902A037F929" box="[1028,1090,1750,1777]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" unit="in" value="23.0">23 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF97FF86B221F903A0A5F928" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1937" box="[1097,1232,1751,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B221F903A0A5F928" box="[1097,1232,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">D. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity id="DD59B7B8FF97FF86B68EF922A524F8C9" box="[230,337,1782,1809]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.112" metricValueMax="7.366" metricValueMin="6.858" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" unit="in" value="28.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="27.0">27–29 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF97FF86B735F923A655F8C8" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[349,544,1782,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B735F923A655F8C8" box="[349,544,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">D. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the wider area superomedia which is about 1.2–1.3 × as wide as long (1.0– 
<quantity id="DD59B7B8FF97FF86B7D8F8C2A581F8E9" box="[432,500,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" unit="in" value="1.1">1.1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF97FF86B797F8C3A6FDF8E8" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1937" box="[511,648,1815,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B797F8C3A6FDF8E8" box="[511,648,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">D. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity id="DD59B7B8FF97FF86B4A1F8C2A734F8E9" box="[713,833,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.905" metricValueMax="2.032" metricValueMin="1.7779999999999998" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" unit="in" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.8 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF97FF86B523F8C3A078F8E8" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[843,1037,1814,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF97FF86B523F8C3A078F8E8" box="[843,1037,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="236">D. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the ovipositor which is about 1.4–1.5 × the length of the hind tibia (
<quantity id="DD59B7B8FF94FF85B545FF7BA7D1FF12" box="[813,932,175,202]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.921" metricValueMax="3.048" metricValueMin="2.794" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="in" value="1.15" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF94FF85B5C5FF64A040FF11" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1937" box="[941,1077,176,201]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF94FF85B5C5FF64A040FF11" box="[941,1077,176,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">D. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity id="DD59B7B8FF94FF85B21CFF7BA4CBFF32" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" metricValueMax="5.588" metricValueMin="4.572" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="in" value="2.0" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2.2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF94FF85B6A1FF04A5FDFF31" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[201,392,207,233]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandibularis">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF94FF85B6A1FF04A5FDFF31" box="[201,392,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">D. mandibularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF94FF85B457FF04A685FF31" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1937" box="[575,752,207,234]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF94FF85B457FF04A62EFF31" box="[575,603,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">D.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF94FF85B4E5FF04A685FF31" box="[653,752,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two basal antennal segments with numerous rows of sensillae (as on 
